 it's a all-you-can-eat place.

45
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:46,200
 So yeah, we loved that.

46
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:51,080
 But how it worked was you get one visit to the buffet table,

47
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,400
 you get as much food as you want,

48
00:01:52,400 --> 00:01:54,120
 and you can bring it back to the table,

49
00:01:54,120 --> 00:01:56,360
 and that was your dinner.

50
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:58,700
 Okay, so we were all there having a good time

51
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:01,680
 and eating away, and there was one kid, though,

52
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,480
 who got way too much food.

53
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,800
 Like, it was just like a ridiculous amount of food.

54
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,720
 Now, do you remember back in the day,

55
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,740
 or back when I was growing up, Pizza Hut, right,

56
00:02:09,740 --> 00:02:11,900
 had the salad bar, right?

57
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:14,240
 Oh, Pizza Hut salad bar, right?

58
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:16,560
 Me going out for Pizza Hut was like, yes, you know,

59
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:18,280
 Saitan, you know, white people food, right?

60
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:20,440
 This is amazing, okay?

61
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:23,360
 But that salad bar, right, you got that really flimsy,

62
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:26,360
 brown, like, bamboo-ish sort of bowl, do you remember that?

63
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,880
 Right, and there was whole art to, like,

64
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,480
 building up the salad, right?

65
00:02:29,480 --> 00:02:31,400
 So you put, like, the potatoes at the bottom

66
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,960
 to get, like, a foundation, right?

67
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:34,560
 Stick some cucumbers on the side

68
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:37,520
 so you could, like, widen the bowl a little bit, right?

69
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,720
 And people would come back,

70
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:41,780
 and it was, like, this huge tower of salad, right?

71
00:02:41,780 --> 00:02:43,720
 But in the end, like, it just got wasted

72
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:44,640
 'cause it was disgusting.

73
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:46,360
 It was like Thousand Island sauce over, like,

74
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,520
 pineapples and raisins and, like,

75
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:50,800
 all this random stuff mashed together.

76
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,000
 It was disgusting.

77
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:53,360
 No one actually liked the salad,

78
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,200
 and I think they just liked seeing how tall

79
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,600
 they could make that tower, right,

80
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,360
 and bringing it back to the table.

81
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,740
 Well, that's kind of what happened, right?

82
00:02:59,740 --> 00:03:01,540
 This kid got all this food, right?

83
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:03,680
 There was so much, so much food that he got.

84
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,640
 He couldn't finish it all.

85
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:06,800
 All right, so I got really upset.

86
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,600
 I was like, what are we gonna do, right?

87
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:11,880
 You've wasted all this food.

88
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,120
 But then I also thought to myself,

89
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:16,040
 okay, there's a teachable moment here, all right?

90
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:19,000
 How am I gonna make this into a life lesson, right?

91
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:19,840
 So it's a true story.

92
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,680
 This is what I did, right?

93
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:21,680
 I told the young guy, he's like,

94
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:23,200
 dude, like, what happened?

95
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,440
 You just wasted all this food.

96
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,480
 And he said to me, yeah, I thought

97
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:27,920
 it was all you can eat, Ellison.

98
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,280
 So, well, yeah, all you can eat

99
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:31,280
 doesn't mean all you can waste, okay?

100
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:33,600
 So, like, what are we gonna do about this?

101
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:34,800
 You know, you didn't eat the food.

102
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,840
 You're gonna have to pay for it now.

103
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,080
 And he starts to panic.

104
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,840
 He's like, well, I didn't do anything wrong, right?

105
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,880
 You said it was all you can eat.

106
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:42,120
 I'm just gonna put the food back.

107
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,840
 He's like, dude, that's disgusting, okay?

108
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,740
 Do not put the food back, okay?

109
00:03:45,740 --> 00:03:46,960
 It's at the table now.

110
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,960
 All right, something's gotta happen.

111
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,260
 And he said, what's gonna happen?

112
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:52,840
 So, I told him, okay, well, the manager's gonna come.

113
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,720
 He's gonna weigh all the food.

114
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:57,140
 And according to how much it weighs,

115
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:58,840
 you're gonna have to pay the penalty

116
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:01,160
 for wasting all this food.

117
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,640
 And then he really starts to panic.

118
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,560
 So, well, how much money are you gonna have to pay?

119
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,560
 Like, my mom didn't give me that much pocket money.

120
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:08,400
 You know, I've been planning to spend on some souvenirs.

121
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,400
 Like, I don't have it.

122
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,440
 Like, what am I gonna do?

123
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:14,620
 So, I told him, okay, the only way you can get out of this

124
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:16,360
 is if you go to the manager

125
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:18,880
 and you beg him for forgiveness, okay?

126
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,240
 Beg him for forgiveness.

127
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:22,560
 Maybe he'll just let you go.

128
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,560
 He's panicking.

129
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,400
 Where is he?

130
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,760
 So, I point to a gentleman

131
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,040
 sitting on the other side of the restaurant.

132
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:29,920
 Okay, that's the manager sitting right there, right?

133
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:32,640
 Now, I've just pointed to a random guy

134
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,040
 minding his business, okay?

135
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:36,260
 He's there having dinner with his family, right?

136
00:04:36,260 --> 00:04:39,960
 Because the truth was, there was no manager, okay?

137
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:41,240
 Who was mad at him.

138
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,140
 I just, like I said, teachable moment.

139
00:04:43,140 --> 00:04:46,340
 I wanted to teach him a lesson to not to waste food.

140
00:04:46,340 --> 00:04:48,980
 Right, so this boy, he stands there for a minute, right?

141
00:04:48,980 --> 00:04:50,180
 And he's like sweating bullets.

142
00:04:50,180 --> 00:04:52,500
 He's like rehearsing what he's gonna say,

143
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,340
 practicing his Mandarin.

144
00:04:53,340 --> 00:04:55,300
 He's like, (mimics Mandarin)

145
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,900
 Right, and so, and then he really like,

146
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:59,660
 coyly walks up to this man, taps him on the shoulder,

147
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:00,900
 and he just starts going for it.

148
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:01,740
 I'm really sorry.

149
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:03,180
 I've ate all this food.

150
00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:04,140
 I don't have money to pay.

151
00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:05,420
 Please forgive me, right?

152
00:05:05,420 --> 00:05:07,820
 And this man's just staring blankly at him like,

153
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:11,500
 why is this kid like confessing all his sins to me

154
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,840
 right now, you know?

155
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,820
 And then, anyway, I was standing in the corner

156
00:05:14,820 --> 00:05:17,020
 also crying, but with laughter, right?

157
00:05:17,020 --> 00:05:19,940
 Like, I'm not saying it was a good thing or a bad thing.

158
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:22,820
 I don't know, but no more food was wasted that trip.

159
00:05:22,820 --> 00:05:23,900
 We'll say it like that, okay?

160
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:28,900
 So, now of course, you know, that's a bit of a funny story.

161
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:31,500
 But in a way, we sort of, we've all been there, right?

162
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,300
 In that moment.

163
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:36,740
 Like that moment when we realize we've done something wrong

164
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:38,820
 and the guilt and the shame and the fear

165
00:05:38,820 --> 00:05:40,460
 that comes with that.

166
00:05:40,460 --> 00:05:42,120
 And then you have this reaction of trying

167
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:44,020
 to make things right, realizing then,

168
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:46,580
 actually, there is nothing I can do to make it right.

169
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:51,540
 The only thing left for me to do is to ask for forgiveness

170
00:05:51,540 --> 00:05:54,840
 and hope that forgiveness is offered to us.

171
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:59,020
 You know, we're at the tail end of the year already,

172
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:00,340
 believe it or not.

173
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:03,180
 And we have Advent starting soon.

174
00:06:03,180 --> 00:06:06,120
 But before Advent, this is our last sermon series

175
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:07,380
 of the year.

176
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:12,380
 And actually, this sermon series was born out of a heart cry

177
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:14,340
 of the community, I believe.

178
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:16,420
 You may remember a few months ago,

179
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:18,860
 we did an event called Converse.

180
00:06:18,860 --> 00:06:20,860
 And at Converse, we set up prayer stations

181
00:06:20,860 --> 00:06:22,900
 up at a high school, you know, just up the hill.

182
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,840
 And there was a big hall and there was all these different,

183
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:27,340
 amazing prayer stations, different ways for us

184
00:06:27,340 --> 00:06:28,980
 to interact with prayer.

185
00:06:28,980 --> 00:06:32,020
 And one of the stations was to do with forgiveness, right?

186
00:06:32,020 --> 00:06:34,540
 It was either asking, you know, prayer requests

187
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:39,380
 to give forgiveness or to receive forgiveness.

188
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:42,540
 And as we looked through the prayer requests

189
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:44,100
 that were written out, we realized, right,

190
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:49,100
 this is a theme that so many of us are struggling with

191
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:50,420
 in our community.

192
00:06:50,420 --> 00:06:54,300
 Many of these had to do with relationships, right?

193
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:58,060
 People asking for the strength to be able to forgive people

194
00:06:58,060 --> 00:07:00,700
 that have hurt them in different ways.

195
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:03,360
 There were also many voices asking for forgiveness

196
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:05,900
 because they have been the ones who have caused harm

197
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:08,320
 and hurt to other people.

198
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:10,140
 A lot of written on there was to, you know,

199
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:12,220
 about forgiving ourselves, right?

200
00:07:12,220 --> 00:07:14,180
 The different things that we struggle with,

201
00:07:14,180 --> 00:07:16,340
 asking God for forgiveness.

202
00:07:16,340 --> 00:07:19,220
 And in some ways, there was also a lot of requests

203
00:07:19,220 --> 00:07:22,700
 asking for, you know, to be able to forgive God, right?

204
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:24,900
 Because people have felt like God has let them down.

205
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,460
 They put their faith in God and they felt like God

206
00:07:26,460 --> 00:07:27,300
 had let them down.

207
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:30,080
 And I feel like I need to forgive God in some way.

208
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:33,660
 And so since this was a topic that so many of us

209
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:36,120
 were wrestling with, we figured it was time

210
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:39,660
 to address this together as a church.

211
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:43,460
 Because the truth is, we all need, everyone needs

212
00:07:43,460 --> 00:07:46,380
 to come to a good understanding of what forgiveness is,

213
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:49,260
 of what forgiveness is and what it's supposed to look like

214
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:53,380
 because forgiveness sits at the center of God's heart.

215
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:58,100
 And forgiveness is essential for our relationship with God.

216
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,020
 In fact, without forgiveness, there would be

217
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:03,180
 no relationship with God possible, right?

218
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:05,900
 At the same time, forgiveness is also essential

219
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:08,840
 for us to be in relationship and in community

220
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:11,000
 with each other.

221
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,800
 Without forgiveness, not even this church, right,

222
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:16,620
 society itself would totally break down

223
00:08:16,620 --> 00:08:18,380
 and we would never be able to do life

224
00:08:18,380 --> 00:08:20,300
 and to connect with each other.

225
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:24,640
 But at the same time, as we've experienced,

226
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:27,660
 it's not that simple.

227
00:08:27,660 --> 00:08:29,080
 Right, because forgiveness is nuanced

228
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:32,880
 with so many different questions and feelings and emotions.

229
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:35,000
 And over these next few weeks, we're gonna face

230
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,680
 some of these questions head on.

231
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:40,440
 We're gonna be talking about some theological framework

232
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:44,440
 about what forgiveness is from the biblical perspective.

233
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,960
 We're gonna be looking at some very practical ways

234
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,140
 of how we can forgive, what forgiveness is

235
00:08:49,140 --> 00:08:51,040
 and what forgiveness isn't.

236
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,600
 We're gonna hear testimonies from our community groups

237
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:57,420
 about how forgiveness has been such an enriching part

238
00:08:57,420 --> 00:09:00,200
 of their relationship with each other.

239
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:01,880
 We're gonna talk about what it means

240
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:03,960
 for us to forgive ourselves.

241
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:06,560
 And in the end, the hope is we're gonna be equipped

242
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:08,400
 to be live out, to be walking out,

243
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:12,960
 to live a life that is defined by forgiveness.

244
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,720
 And so to start us on our journey today,

245
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:17,440
 I want to look at a passage that teaches us,

246
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:20,320
 you know, that I think really Jesus uses this passage

247
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:23,880
 to highlight just how important forgiveness is

248
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:26,060
 from his perspective and how he hopes

249
00:09:26,060 --> 00:09:29,040
 his followers will respond to it.

250
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:31,440
 Okay, we're looking at Matthew chapter 18,

251
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:33,560
 verses 21 to 35.

252
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,760
 I'm gonna read it and you can follow along.

253
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:38,800
 Then Peter came to Jesus and asked,

254
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:42,880
 "Lord, how many times shall I forgive my brother or sister

255
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:44,480
 "who sins against me?

256
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:47,040
 "Up to seven times?"

257
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:49,940
 Jesus answered, "I tell you, not seven times,

258
00:09:49,940 --> 00:09:52,820
 "but 77 times.

259
00:09:52,820 --> 00:09:54,760
 "Therefore, the kingdom of heaven is like a king

