00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:18,400
 Right, and so Jesus tries to illustrate this

496
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:21,160
 in the way the master responds to his servant.

497
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:23,840
 At this, the servant fell on his knees before him.

498
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:25,560
 "Be patient with me," he begged,

499
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:28,140
 "and I will pay everything back."

500
00:20:28,140 --> 00:20:30,240
 The servant's master took pity on him,

501
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:33,600
 "Cancel the debt and let him go."

502
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:38,360
 This man realizes, right, his inevitable doom.

