00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:22,500
 "I'm never gonna do that again,

520
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,940
 "I'm never gonna do this again."

521
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:27,940
 But what I found in my life is that the more I try,

522
00:21:27,940 --> 00:21:29,820
 even though I try and I try and try,

523
00:21:29,820 --> 00:21:33,360
 the harder I try, it's almost like the harder we fail.

524
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:36,200
 And I've slowly come to the realization

525
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:40,260
 that through our own power, through our own will,

526
00:21:40,260 --> 00:21:42,580
 we will never, ever, ever, ever be able

527
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:45,160
 to pay back the debt of sin.

528
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:51,780
 And the master realizes this, and God realizes this.

529
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:53,520
 And even though he has the right and authority

530
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:56,500
 to divide some sort of payment,

531
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:59,160
 something really beautiful happens.

532
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:03,980
 This phrase, "The servant's master took pity on him."

533
00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:07,700
 The word pity here means like love actually and compassion.

534
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:11,180
 Not because the servant has done anything

535
00:22:11,180 --> 00:22:15,180
 to deserve a pardon, but because of the master's heart

536
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:18,980
 of love and compassion, the debt is canceled

537
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:20,640
 and he is set free.

538
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:23,920
 And considering the amount of debt he was owed,

539
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:25,800
 this was unimaginable, right?

540
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:28,160
 The listeners of Jesus's time listening to this,

541
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:30,160
 were like, "This guy must be crazy

542
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:33,080
 "to just let all that money go."

543
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:36,080
 But this is the master saying, "What matters to me

544
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:38,640
 "is not the amount of money that he owes.

545
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:42,440
 "I'm trying to demonstrate my heart of grace,

546
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:45,460
 "of mercy, of compassion, and of love."

547
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:49,820
 And the servant walks away in freedom.

548
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:53,680
 And this is Jesus reminding us, right?

549
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:57,920
 This is an echo of God's message of forgiveness of sin.

550
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,700
 Actually, this is a message that God has said

551
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:02,240
 time and time and time again.

552
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:04,200
 We see God's heart to forgive.

553
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:07,160
 Throughout the Old Testament even, Isaiah 43, 25,

554
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:10,440
 "I will blot out your transgressions."

555
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:13,740
 Jeremiah 31, 34, "I will forgive their wickedness

556
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:16,100
 "and remember their sins no more."

557
00:23:16,100 --> 00:23:19,200
 Psalm 103, 12, one of my favorite passages,

558
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,720
 "As as far the east is from the west,

559
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:26,720
 "so far has he removed our transgressions from us."

560
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:29,720
 This is our starting point, church.

561
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:31,180
 Never forget this.

562
00:23:31,180 --> 00:23:37,200
 God's heart is one that is inclined towards forgiveness.

563
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:40,720
 His heart is one of compassion and of love.

564
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:43,600
 This is what we were singing over and over and over again

565
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:44,720
 this morning, right?

566
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:48,000
 His heart is that despite the fact that we have wronged him,

567
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:50,520
 we have disappointed him, we have sinned in our lives,

568
00:23:50,520 --> 00:23:53,640
 we have missed the mark, we have gone against his will,

569
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,640
 despite that many times we make a mess of things,

570
00:23:56,640 --> 00:24:00,600
 God still looks on us with love and compassion, amen?

571
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:03,640
 And God loved us so much,

572
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:07,760
 he gave us his most precious gift, his son,

573
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:10,800
 as the only way to repay the debt of sin.

574
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:14,360
 God gave us his son, paying the debt of our sins

575
00:24:14,360 --> 00:24:17,040
 so that we can have relationship with him.

576
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:19,240
 Again, this is something we're gonna talk more about

577
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:21,060
 next week and in the weeks to come.

578
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:25,000
 But what we need to understand for today is this,

579
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:28,440
 is we who worship the true God are a people

580
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:32,120
 who have had all their debt forgiven

581
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:35,000
 because our master loves us.

582
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,560
 Forgiveness, therefore, is important

583
00:24:37,560 --> 00:24:41,280
 because it's the key not just to this life,

584
00:24:41,280 --> 00:24:44,720
 but to eternal life as well.

585
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,440
 This is what I mean when I say forgiveness

586
00:24:46,440 --> 00:24:48,080
 sits at the very heart of God

587
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:51,440
 and encapsulates all that he came to do,

588
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:56,280
 was to offer forgiveness for you, for me,

589
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:59,560
 for anyone who asks of it.

590
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:02,640
 If you are a follower of Jesus in this room today,

591
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:07,520
 you are free because you have received God's forgiveness.

592
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:11,720
 Now, as a people who've understood

593
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:15,080
 and experienced this wonderful gift of forgiveness,

594
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:18,400
 you would think that we would now want to share

595
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,360
 this gift with others as well,

596
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:23,160
 like last week when we were talking about the gospel.

597
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:25,600
 But again, it's hard and it's complicated.

598
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:28,880
 It doesn't always work this way.

599
00:25:28,880 --> 00:25:30,360
 And for the servant on this story,

600
00:25:30,360 --> 00:25:32,640
 we find that though, even though he is the one

601
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:36,040
 who has experienced the forgiveness of a great debt,

602
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:38,360
 his own heart remains unchanged.

603
00:25:38,360 --> 00:25:42,360
 It tells us this, but when that servant went out,

604
00:25:42,360 --> 00:25:44,180
 he found one of his fellow servants

605
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:46,400
 who owed him 100 silver coins.

606
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:48,480
 He grabbed him and began to choke him.

607
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:51,360
 "Pay back what you owe me," he demanded.

608
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:54,440
 His fellow servant fell to his knees and begged him,

609
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:58,280
 "Be patient with me and I will pay it back."

610
00:25:58,280 --> 00:25:59,800
 But he refused.

611
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:03,080
 Instead, he went off and had that man thrown in prison

612
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:04,760
 until he could pay the debt.

613
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:09,680
 You see, when this man encounters someone who owes him money,

614
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:12,160
 his heart is not full of compassion.

615
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:16,140
 He remains tight-fisted and stingy about what he's owed.

616
00:26:16,140 --> 00:26:19,980
 100 silver coins, okay, I said just now,

617
00:26:19,980 --> 00:26:23,220
 you know that 10,000 bags of gold was like a gazillion

618
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:26,460
 dollars, 100 silver coins would have been about maybe

619
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:28,700
 the equivalent of four months wages, right,

620
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:30,120
 the Bible scholars say.

621
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:32,160
 Not a small sum in and of itself, right,

622
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:35,100
 but not insurmountable as well, right?

623
00:26:35,100 --> 00:26:38,000
 But compared to what he owed, right,

624
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,580
 completely insignificant.

625
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:41,880
 And this dialogue that he has, right,

626
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:45,240
 it's almost an exact replica of what just happened with him

627
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:47,720
 and his master, right, there's a debt,

628
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:48,960
 there's a falling to the knees,

629
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:51,600
 begging for patience and mercy.

630
00:26:51,600 --> 00:26:54,360
 But like I said, the difference is that there's no mention

631
00:26:54,360 --> 00:26:57,720
 of compassion from this servant's heart.

632
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:00,000
 Instead, it's the opposite.

633
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:03,920
 Listen to this term, he said he refused.

634
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:07,040
 When it says refused, this word means to sort of like

635
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:08,720
 harden his heart, right?

636
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:11,340
 He made a conscious decision in his mind,

637
00:27:11,340 --> 00:27:14,260
 I am not willing, I'm going to make a choice

638
00:27:14,260 --> 00:27:17,040
 not to forgive this person.

639
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:19,100
 And actually, it gets even worse.

640
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:22,940
 Not only does he refuse, but he tries to take actions

641
00:27:22,940 --> 00:27:24,660
 into his own hands, right?

642
00:27:24,660 --> 00:27:27,380
 He escalates, he purposely, first of all,

643
00:27:27,380 --> 00:27:30,300
 goes out of his way to seek out this person who owes him.

644
00:27:30,300 --> 00:27:33,700
 And when he finds him, it says he physically abuses him,

645
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:37,020
 right, he grabs him and he chokes him.

646
00:27:37,020 --> 00:27:39,220
 He takes matters into his own hands.

647
00:27:39,220 --> 00:27:43,660
 As you read this story, you probably, as I was,

648
00:27:43,660 --> 00:27:45,340
 judging this guy right now, right?

649
00:27:45,340 --> 00:27:49,380
 Wow, how evil, how wicked is this man

650
00:27:49,380 --> 00:27:51,920
 that he would do something like this?

651
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:57,100
 Now, before we get too judgmental of this servant,

652
00:27:57,100 --> 00:28:00,220
 and as uncomfortable as this might make us,

653
00:28:00,220 --> 00:28:02,420
 maybe we need to lean into this part of the story

654
00:28:02,420 --> 00:28:03,780
 a little bit.

655
00:28:03,780 --> 00:28:05,700
 And I found it helpful, instead of judging it

656
00:28:05,700 --> 00:28:10,380
 from the outside, to use this scenario more like a mirror

657
00:28:10,380 --> 00:28:13,260
 to check my own attitude toward forgiveness.

658
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:15,660
 And maybe it's a bit more like this servant

659
00:28:15,660 --> 00:28:16,700
 than we think it is.

660
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:20,940
 Because like I said just now, when we've been sinned against

661
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:25,540
 our first reaction is more likely inclined towards revenge.

662
00:28:25,540 --> 00:28:28,940
 We want to see people suffer, right,

663
00:28:28,940 --> 00:28:32,080
 and get what they deserve when they sin against us.

664
00:28:33,140 --> 00:28:36,580
 I admit to you in my own heart, this is often what I feel.

665
00:28:36,580 --> 00:28:38,980
 I want to be able to enjoy all of God's forgiveness.

666
00:28:38,980 --> 00:28:40,660
 Yes, I want to be able to come to God,

667
00:28:40,660 --> 00:28:43,040
 ask for his forgiveness, and receive his compassion

668
00:28:43,040 --> 00:28:45,020
 and mercy and grace.

669
00:28:45,020 --> 00:28:47,180
 But sometimes when people sin against me,

670
00:28:47,180 --> 00:28:49,740
 my first reaction is not, Father, forgive them.

671
00:28:49,740 --> 00:28:51,880
 My reaction is, I hope they suffer.

672
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:56,820
 I hope God punished them for what they did to me.

673
00:28:56,820 --> 00:29:00,660
 In fact, I hope they first, they experience 10 times worse

674
00:29:00,660 --> 00:29:01,720
 than what they did to me.

675
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:03,140
 That's what they deserve.

676
00:29:03,140 --> 00:29:06,860
 I know I'm not alone in this.

677
00:29:06,860 --> 00:29:10,340
 But this is precisely why this whole series

678
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:13,820
 and this conversation on forgiveness is important

679
00:29:13,820 --> 00:29:15,820
 for us to have together.

680
00:29:15,820 --> 00:29:20,180
 Because now Jesus starts to talk about the consequences

681
00:29:20,180 --> 00:29:22,440
 of our debt when we don't forgive.

682
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:26,960
 Jesus needs to be saying, unless you learn to forgive

683
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:29,940
 that you have been forgiven, there are gonna be

684
00:29:29,940 --> 00:29:33,640
 consequences, and these consequences affect both

685
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:37,960
 the wider community, but also your own relationship

686
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,760
 with God as well.

687
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:43,640
 Let me tell you how it leaves a strain

688
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:45,520
 on the community, first of all.

689
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:47,600
 When the other servants saw what had happened,

690
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:50,600
 they were outraged and went and told their master

691
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:54,080
 everything that has happened, that had happened.

692
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:57,480
 All right, this is why I said this is a heart cry

693
00:29:57,480 --> 00:29:58,320
 of the church.

694
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:00,700
 This is why I said we're gonna take this journey together

695
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:02,680
 as a community, as a body of Christ,

696
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:05,140
 as a family of brothers and sisters.

697
00:30:05,140 --> 00:30:08,040
 Because often when we talk about forgiveness,

698
00:30:08,040 --> 00:30:11,700
 we tend to look at it individualistically.

699
00:30:11,700 --> 00:30:13,820
 That's just between two people.

700
00:30:13,820 --> 00:30:17,980
 It doesn't concern the rest of the community.

701
00:30:17,980 --> 00:30:20,140
 So let's say me and Derek here had beef.

702
00:30:20,140 --> 00:30:21,880
 We had a problem with each other.

703
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:26,340
 If people find out, just leave the Eric,

704
00:30:26,340 --> 00:30:28,240
 Ellison and Derek can figure that out by themselves,

705
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:29,800
 it doesn't concern us.

706
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:32,160
 But actually it does.

707
00:30:32,160 --> 00:30:36,300
 I think as a body of Christ, we all need to agree

708
00:30:36,300 --> 00:30:39,240
 that forgiveness is a poison.

709
00:30:39,240 --> 00:30:41,360
 And that if we don't deal with it,

710
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:44,200
 there is no way we can ever be the body of Christ

711
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:45,740
 that he has called us to be.

712
00:30:45,740 --> 00:30:48,660
 How are we supposed to walk alongside each other

713
00:30:48,660 --> 00:30:50,520
 if we're not willing to forgive?

714
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:52,720
 How are we supposed to grow in intimacy

715
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:55,720
 if we hold grudges against each other?

716
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,460
 How are we gonna encourage each other

717
00:30:57,460 --> 00:31:00,500
 if we keep account of what's right and what's wrong?

718
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:01,780
 Every time we've wronged and right,

719
00:31:01,780 --> 00:31:04,620
 we keep an account of the rights and wrongs.

720
00:31:04,620 --> 00:31:08,460
 Therefore, as a community, we need to be aware of this.

721
00:31:08,460 --> 00:31:12,620
 And as a community, if we see unforgiveness taking place,

722
00:31:12,620 --> 00:31:14,900
 we need to do something about it

723
00:31:14,900 --> 00:31:18,500
 so it doesn't corrupt the rest of the body of Christ.

724
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:20,000
 We need to call it out.

725
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:22,860
 What also points out is the community then,

726
00:31:22,860 --> 00:31:24,880
 it's supposed to be a place of safety

727
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:26,520
 and of accountability.

728
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:29,060
 You see, if no one else had got involved,

729
00:31:29,060 --> 00:31:31,740
 the servant would have got away with his actions.

730
00:31:31,740 --> 00:31:33,860
 He would have got away with abusing his debtor,

731
00:31:33,860 --> 00:31:35,420
 having him thrown in jail,

732
00:31:35,420 --> 00:31:37,880
 punished for something like that.

733
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:40,360
 But notice, it was the other servants

734
00:31:40,360 --> 00:31:42,820
 who called him out of his sin.

735
00:31:42,820 --> 00:31:44,100
 Right, it was the other servants,

736
00:31:44,100 --> 00:31:46,380
 the community around him that flagged to the master,

737
00:31:46,380 --> 00:31:49,060
 hey, something isn't quite right here.

738
00:31:49,060 --> 00:31:52,800
 And we need to do and say something about it.

739
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:58,820
 So when it comes to forgiveness,

740
00:31:58,820 --> 00:32:01,580
 we see forgiveness and justice is something

741
00:32:01,580 --> 00:32:04,700
 that actually go hand in hand with each other.

742
00:32:04,700 --> 00:32:08,260
 Forgiveness doesn't mean that one's causing harm,

743
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:10,720
 can just get away with it.

744
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:13,620
 But forgiveness is what happens when a community,

745
00:32:13,620 --> 00:32:16,500
 when somebody is wrong and the community around you

746
00:32:16,500 --> 00:32:18,220
 comes around you to support you,

747
00:32:18,220 --> 00:32:22,140
 to give you strength and power to confront the wrong

748
00:32:22,140 --> 00:32:24,140
 and it's voiced out.

749
00:32:24,140 --> 00:32:26,000
 You see what I'm saying?

750
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,540
 Community and forgiveness doesn't mean saying

751
00:32:28,540 --> 00:32:29,820
 it really didn't happen, right?

752
00:32:29,820 --> 00:32:32,660
 It really doesn't matter, just let it go.

753
00:32:32,660 --> 00:32:33,820
 Right, in either of those cases,

754
00:32:33,820 --> 00:32:35,680
 if it didn't matter, you just let it go,

755
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:37,480
 you don't need forgiveness.

756
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:38,980
 Right, maybe it's just a misunderstanding

757
00:32:38,980 --> 00:32:41,120
 that needs to be cleared up.

758
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:43,860
 But forgiveness is the process when we admit,

759
00:32:43,860 --> 00:32:47,940
 yes, something did happen, it did matter,

760
00:32:47,940 --> 00:32:51,700
 something has gone wrong and we need to deal with it.

761
00:32:51,700 --> 00:32:55,260
 And we deal with it together as a body of Christ.

762
00:32:55,260 --> 00:32:57,740
 But the way we deal with it is to hand it over to God,

763
00:32:57,740 --> 00:32:59,540
 to say we're not God.

764
00:32:59,540 --> 00:33:03,180
 We don't get to set the standard of who is worthy

765
00:33:03,180 --> 00:33:05,220
 of forgiveness or who is not.

766
00:33:05,220 --> 00:33:09,460
 We simply offer forgiveness first.

767
00:33:09,460 --> 00:33:12,980
 Because without that, we will never be able to move on

768
00:33:12,980 --> 00:33:15,520
 as individuals and as a community.

769
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:21,120
 So that's how it affects us together as a body of Christ.

770
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:25,120
 On the same time though, it has an individual impact

771
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:27,060
 on us as well.

772
00:33:27,060 --> 00:33:29,440
 And God spells out very clearly the results

773
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:31,180
 of withholding forgiveness.

774
00:33:31,180 --> 00:33:34,860
 Then the master called the servant in.

775
00:33:34,860 --> 00:33:37,180
 You wicked servant, he said.

776
00:33:37,180 --> 00:33:42,140
 I canceled all that debt of yours because you begged me to.

777
00:33:42,140 --> 00:33:44,820
 Shouldn't you have had mercy on your fellow servant

778
00:33:44,820 --> 00:33:47,180
 just as I had on you?

779
00:33:47,180 --> 00:33:49,660
 In his anger, the master handed him over to the jailers

780
00:33:49,660 --> 00:33:53,940
 to be tortured until he should pay back all that he owed.

781
00:33:53,940 --> 00:33:56,900
 This is how my heavenly father will treat each of you

782
00:33:56,900 --> 00:34:01,780
 unless you forgive your brother or sister from your heart.

783
00:34:01,780 --> 00:34:05,280
 Again, this sounds harsh.

784
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:08,460
 But I think the point scripture is trying to make is this.

785
00:34:08,460 --> 00:34:11,700
 It might seem like when we don't offer forgiveness,

786
00:34:11,700 --> 00:34:15,820
 that we hold onto the power, that we hold onto the control.

787
00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:17,900
 But when in reality, what Jesus is saying is

788
00:34:17,900 --> 00:34:20,320
 when we withhold forgiveness,

789
00:34:20,320 --> 00:34:23,080
 it's actually a great detriment to us.

790
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:28,280
 It seems like the other person is getting what they deserve.

791
00:34:28,280 --> 00:34:31,900
 But in reality, what we're doing is condemning ourselves.

792
00:34:31,900 --> 00:34:34,700
 You might know the old saying,

793
00:34:34,700 --> 00:34:36,940
 unforgiveness is like drinking a poison

794
00:34:36,940 --> 00:34:38,900
 and expecting the other person to die.

795
00:34:40,860 --> 00:34:44,580
 Right, so it has really, really serious consequences

796
00:34:44,580 --> 00:34:47,940
 for ourselves if we withhold forgiveness.

797
00:34:47,940 --> 00:34:50,780
 Maybe you could think about it this way.

798
00:34:50,780 --> 00:34:53,460
 We're gonna do a little exercise together.

799
00:34:53,460 --> 00:34:54,720
 Okay, on the count of three,

800
00:34:54,720 --> 00:34:56,660
 I want everybody to take a deep breath.

801
00:34:56,660 --> 00:34:58,420
 Okay, when you take a deep breath,

802
00:34:58,420 --> 00:35:00,700
 hold it in for as long as you can.

803
00:35:00,700 --> 00:35:02,940
 Right, try and hold your breath, okay?

804
00:35:02,940 --> 00:35:05,700
 One, two, three.

805
00:35:05,820 --> 00:35:07,980
 [inhales]

806
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:23,340
 Some of us might be able to do this for longer, right?

807
00:35:23,340 --> 00:35:26,500
 But you're probably feeling a struggle to breathe now, right?

808
00:35:26,500 --> 00:35:29,260
 To breathe out that breath.

809
00:35:29,260 --> 00:35:31,420
 Right, none of us, nobody in this room

810
00:35:31,420 --> 00:35:33,880
 is able to hold their breath forever.

811
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:34,900
 You would either pass out

812
00:35:34,900 --> 00:35:37,500
 or if you really did just stop breathing altogether,

813
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:38,380
 you would die.

814
00:35:38,380 --> 00:35:42,820
 In order for you to take your next breath,

815
00:35:42,820 --> 00:35:45,840
 you have to release the breath you're holding.

816
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:49,380
 And so it is with forgiveness.

817
00:35:49,380 --> 00:35:53,860
 If we want to receive forgiveness,

818
00:35:53,860 --> 00:35:57,660
 we need to be able to release forgiveness to others as well.

819
00:35:57,660 --> 00:36:04,540
 Like I said, though, this is the starting point.

820
00:36:05,180 --> 00:36:08,300
 Right, this is just the introduction to this journey.

821
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:11,100
 And there's no way we can unpack and discover

822
00:36:11,100 --> 00:36:14,340
 all the things that forgiveness means for us

823
00:36:14,340 --> 00:36:17,440
 in one short sermon on a Sunday morning.

824
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:21,380
 So I want to encourage everybody here.

825
00:36:21,380 --> 00:36:23,220
 Please try to come along, right,

826
00:36:23,220 --> 00:36:25,660
 to the next few messages that we have,

827
00:36:25,660 --> 00:36:27,300
 to the next few Sundays that we have

828
00:36:27,300 --> 00:36:30,100
 in this journey of forgiveness.

829
00:36:30,100 --> 00:36:31,160
 And this is not about, you know,

830
00:36:31,160 --> 00:36:32,780
 like maintaining numbers at the vine

831
00:36:32,780 --> 00:36:33,620
 or anything like that, right?

832
00:36:33,620 --> 00:36:34,780
 It's not about that.

833
00:36:34,780 --> 00:36:38,180
 But what this is, it's for your wholeness.

834
00:36:38,180 --> 00:36:39,860
 It's for your understanding.

835
00:36:39,860 --> 00:36:42,100
 It's for you to really be able to embrace

836
00:36:42,100 --> 00:36:44,540
 what forgiveness means so you can walk

837
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:47,520
 in the freedom of forgiveness.

838
00:36:47,520 --> 00:36:50,820
 After all, Jesus taught us to pray.

839
00:36:50,820 --> 00:36:55,620
 Forgive our sins as we forgive those

840
00:36:55,620 --> 00:36:57,800
 who have sinned against us.

841
00:36:57,800 --> 00:37:03,580
 And my heart is, as individuals,

842
00:37:03,580 --> 00:37:05,980
 but also as a community, we will embrace

843
00:37:05,980 --> 00:37:08,420
 this journey of forgiveness together.

844
00:37:08,420 --> 00:37:11,060
 To step by step, learn what it means

845
00:37:11,060 --> 00:37:15,340
 to receive and to give out what forgiveness

846
00:37:15,340 --> 00:37:17,080
 really means in God's heart.

847
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:21,340
 This is how we build, continue the kingdom of God

848
00:37:21,340 --> 00:37:22,580
 here on this earth.

849
00:37:22,580 --> 00:37:27,400
 So would you pray with me as we start this journey together?

850
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:29,660
 [coughing]

851
00:37:29,660 --> 00:37:45,200
 Jesus, we know that this is an issue

852
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:46,960
 that many of us are wrestling with.

853
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:50,080
 And even if we're not wrestling with it

854
00:37:50,080 --> 00:37:52,400
 right at this moment, there is gonna come a time

855
00:37:52,400 --> 00:37:56,320
 where we've been wronged and we need to offer forgiveness.

856
00:37:56,320 --> 00:38:00,080
 Or someone wrongs us, or we wrong someone else

857
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:03,340
 and we need to be forgiven.

858
00:38:03,340 --> 00:38:09,400
 And so Lord, I thank you that.

859
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:12,560
 Our starting point, Lord, is that you have already

860
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:15,240
 poured forgiveness out for us.

861
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:17,120
 That you have offered forgiveness to us

862
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:20,620
 despite our sin, despite the ways that we've missed

863
00:38:20,620 --> 00:38:23,200
 the mark when it comes to being in relationship

864
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:24,040
 with you, Lord.

865
00:38:25,300 --> 00:38:28,760
 You've given us everything we need,

866
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:32,820
 your most precious gift so that we can have forgiveness.

867
00:38:32,820 --> 00:38:36,800
 Lord, as we receive this gift, Lord,

868
00:38:36,800 --> 00:38:42,940
 we hear that you've also asked us to pour it out

869
00:38:42,940 --> 00:38:44,580
 to those who have wronged us.

870
00:38:44,580 --> 00:38:50,480
 And I know this is a hard journey for some of us to take.

871
00:38:55,180 --> 00:38:56,220
 You might be thinking right now,

872
00:38:56,220 --> 00:39:00,040
 if you only knew the pain that I've been through,

873
00:39:00,040 --> 00:39:04,380
 what this person did to me, how that person hurt me.

874
00:39:04,380 --> 00:39:12,020
 And Father, we know that you meet us

875
00:39:12,020 --> 00:39:13,440
 in those areas of pain.

876
00:39:13,440 --> 00:39:21,120
 And so Jesus, I pray that through your gentle guidance

877
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:23,900
 in the way that only you know how you would teach us

878
00:39:24,500 --> 00:39:27,700
 how to forgive.

879
00:39:27,700 --> 00:39:32,580
 That as we embrace forgiveness in our own hearts,

880
00:39:32,580 --> 00:39:34,180
 it would soften our hearts.

881
00:39:34,180 --> 00:39:44,740
 And as we learn to live a life defined by forgiveness,

882
00:39:44,740 --> 00:39:46,880
 we will reflect your gospel, your grace,

883
00:39:46,880 --> 00:39:48,420
 your mercy to everybody.

884
00:39:48,420 --> 00:39:52,820
 And that even together as a community,

885
00:39:52,820 --> 00:39:56,460
 we can keep encouraging each other in this journey,

886
00:39:56,460 --> 00:40:00,580
 keep encouraging each other to not keep things hidden,

887
00:40:00,580 --> 00:40:04,060
 but to bring it out into the light when there's been sin,

888
00:40:04,060 --> 00:40:05,620
 when there's been wrong in the community.

889
00:40:05,620 --> 00:40:10,620
 We will not let that just be swept under the carpet.

890
00:40:10,620 --> 00:40:12,640
 But Lord, because we know the proper way

891
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:17,020
 to deal with these things, we can walk with it together.

892
00:40:20,500 --> 00:40:23,020
 And that this forgiveness that we offer to each other

893
00:40:23,020 --> 00:40:26,720
 reflects, truly reflects the heart that you have for us.

894
00:40:26,720 --> 00:40:31,380
 So Lord, be with us the next few weeks

895
00:40:31,380 --> 00:40:33,100
 as we walk through this.

896
00:40:33,100 --> 00:40:35,200
 Encourage us, strengthen us, guide us.

897
00:40:35,200 --> 00:40:38,540
 We pray this in Jesus' name, amen.

